{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HF3XQar4gVM7mUmdQFcDH9","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"80ecde4e-3ccc-44de-925d-a2036bf845d1","uuid":"b21f1ebf-32e6-46b1-a6c9-3165750f50b1","timestamp":"2026-04-03T21:09:52.050Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"update","filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-04\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":106,"newStart":1,"newLines":1,"lines":["-# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-04 (Session 3)","-","-### 17-2-lane-pool — create-story (2026-04-04T20:04)","-","-- Sprint-status.yaml showed 17-1-worktree-manager regressed to `backlog` despite being committed as `done`. Fixed manually.","-- All 12 ACs tagged `test-provable` — pure scheduling module with mocked deps.","-- AC #5 epic independence ordering is simplified heuristic; post-MVP DAG approach noted.","-","-## Token Report","-- Total tool calls: 14","-- By tool: Read: 6, Glob: 6, Grep: 2, Bash: 1, Write: 1","-- Largest Bash outputs: `ls implementation-artifacts` (~5 lines)","-- Files read: 6 unique, 6 total reads","-- Redundant operations: 3 similar glob patterns for story files","-","-### 17-2-lane-pool — dev-story (2026-04-04T20:16)","-","-- Epic independence semantics (AC #5): batch-style parallelism, not sliding-window. Epic 3 won't start until ALL preceding epics complete, even if epic 1 finishes while epic 2 is still running. Matches spec but may surprise users.","-- No workarounds or TODOs.","-- Empty catch blocks annotated with `// IGNORE:` per project lint rules.","-","-## Token Report","-- Total tool calls: 20","-- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 7, Edit: 4, Grep: 3, Write: 2, Glob: 2, Skill: 1","-- Largest Bash outputs: `npm test` (~30 lines), first test run failure (~45 lines), `npx vitest run` (~15 lines)","-- Files read: 9 unique, 9 total reads","-- Redundant operations: none","-","-### 17-2-lane-pool — code-review (2026-04-04T20:22)","-","-- 0 HIGH, 3 MEDIUM (all coverage gaps — fixed), 3 LOW (unreachable defensive code)","-- Coverage after fixes: 100% statements, 91.17% branches, 100% functions, 100% lines","-- LOW: Unreachable `?? 'Unknown error'` fallback and `activeIndex !== undefined` guard — defensive but unnecessary","-- LOW: No test for pool reuse (calling startPool twice)","-- Architecture note: candidate batching bypasses independence check for initial batch — fine for small maxParallel but could over-schedule with large values","-- createWorktree uses execSync, blocking event loop — inherited from WorktreeManager design","-","-## Token Report","-- Total tool calls: 17","-- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 6, Edit: 3, Grep: 1, Glob: 1, Skill: 1","-- Largest Bash outputs: coverage run (~50 lines), verbose test run (~40 lines), coverage run 2 (~30 lines)","-- Files read: 8 unique, 9 total reads","-- Redundant operations: none","-","-### 17-3-run-command-parallel-integration — code-review (2026-04-04T21:03)","-","-- **HIGH**: 20+ TypeScript compilation errors in `run-parallel.test.ts` — mock types wrong, stale @ts-expect-error, spread argument patterns invalid. All fixed.","-- **HIGH**: Mock wrappers used `...(args as [])` cast that silently dropped arguments. Fixed.","-- **MEDIUM**: `poolInstance.onEvent` accessed as `unknown` type. Fixed.","-- **LOW (unfixed)**: `executeFn` ignores `epicId` parameter — each worktree runs full workflow. Deferred to Epic 18/19.","-- **LOW (unfixed)**: `countStories` dual import/re-export pattern in `run.ts`.","-- Coverage: 96.7% overall (PASS), all files above 80% floor.","-","-## Token Report","-- Total tool calls: 24","-- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 9, Edit: 8, Grep: 3, Glob: 1, Skill: 1","-- Largest Bash outputs: `npx tsc --noEmit` (~30 lines), `git diff --name-only` (~29 lines), `git status --porcelain` (~21 lines)","-- Files read: 11 unique, 13 total reads (`run-parallel.test.ts` read 3x)","-- Redundant operations: TSC run 3 times for incremental fix verification","-","----","-","-### 17-3-run-command-parallel-integration — dev-story (2026-04-04T20:55)","-","-- **Vitest mock pattern**: `vi.fn()` mocks cannot be used with `new` via `mockReturnValue`. Had to create actual ES classes in hoisted block that delegate to mutable factory functions. Non-obvious pattern.","-- **File length**: `run.ts` grew from 203 to 340 lines. Story notes NFR9 max 300 lines per file. Could extract parallel path to `run-parallel.ts`.","-- **No integration test with real LanePool/WorktreeManager**: All tests mock pool and worktree manager. Real end-to-end behavior not tested at this level.","-","-## Token Report","-- Total tool calls: 30","-- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 10, Edit: 18, Grep: 2, Write: 1, Glob: 1","-- Largest Bash outputs: `npx tsc --noEmit` (~33 lines), `npx vitest run run-parallel.test.ts` (~40 lines), `npx vitest run` grep (~22 lines)","-- Files read: 10 unique, 11 total reads","-- Redundant operations: None significant","-","----","-","-### 17-3-run-command-parallel-integration — create-story (2026-04-04T20:42)","-","-- No ambiguities in epic definition.","-- Workaround: `--resume` + parallel mode edge case not covered — deferred to Epic 18/19.","-- Risk: executeFn agent resolution is shared across worktrees — fine while agents are stateless config objects.","-- Observation: Docker pre-flight check preserved in parallel path (harmless but unnecessary).","-","-## Token Report","-- Total tool calls: 16","-- By tool: Bash: 1, Read: 7, Grep: 5, Write: 1, Glob: 5","-- Largest Bash outputs: `ls implementation-artifacts` (~230 lines)","-- Files read: 9 unique, 9 total reads","-- Redundant operations: None","-","----","-","-### 17-2-lane-pool — verification (2026-04-04T20:31)","-","-- **`codeharness verify` precondition failure**: AGENTS.md for `src/lib` did not reference `lane-pool.ts`. Fixed by adding entry to AGENTS.md.","-- **BATS test warnings**: `npm test` output polluted with BW01 warnings from BATS integration tests. Pre-existing.","-- **Branch coverage 91.17%**: Uncovered branches at lines 291-306, 398 (defensive fallbacks). Stmts/funcs/lines all 100%.","-- **Verification gap**: AC5 (epic independence) verified by single test with 3 epics.","-","-## Token Report","-- Total tool calls: 14","-- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 3, Write: 1","-- Largest Bash outputs: `npx vitest run --coverage` (~80 lines), `npm test` (~60 lines)","-- Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads","-- Redundant operations: npm test ran twice, coverage command ran twice","+# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-04"]}],"originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-04 (Session 3)\n\n### 17-2-lane-pool — create-story (2026-04-04T20:04)\n\n- Sprint-status.yaml showed 17-1-worktree-manager regressed to `backlog` despite being committed as `done`. Fixed manually.\n- All 12 ACs tagged `test-provable` — pure scheduling module with mocked deps.\n- AC #5 epic independence ordering is simplified heuristic; post-MVP DAG approach noted.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 14\n- By tool: Read: 6, Glob: 6, Grep: 2, Bash: 1, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `ls implementation-artifacts` (~5 lines)\n- Files read: 6 unique, 6 total reads\n- Redundant operations: 3 similar glob patterns for story files\n\n### 17-2-lane-pool — dev-story (2026-04-04T20:16)\n\n- Epic independence semantics (AC #5): batch-style parallelism, not sliding-window. Epic 3 won't start until ALL preceding epics complete, even if epic 1 finishes while epic 2 is still running. Matches spec but may surprise users.\n- No workarounds or TODOs.\n- Empty catch blocks annotated with `// IGNORE:` per project lint rules.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 20\n- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 7, Edit: 4, Grep: 3, Write: 2, Glob: 2, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npm test` (~30 lines), first test run failure (~45 lines), `npx vitest run` (~15 lines)\n- Files read: 9 unique, 9 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 17-2-lane-pool — code-review (2026-04-04T20:22)\n\n- 0 HIGH, 3 MEDIUM (all coverage gaps — fixed), 3 LOW (unreachable defensive code)\n- Coverage after fixes: 100% statements, 91.17% branches, 100% functions, 100% lines\n- LOW: Unreachable `?? 'Unknown error'` fallback and `activeIndex !== undefined` guard — defensive but unnecessary\n- LOW: No test for pool reuse (calling startPool twice)\n- Architecture note: candidate batching bypasses independence check for initial batch — fine for small maxParallel but could over-schedule with large values\n- createWorktree uses execSync, blocking event loop — inherited from WorktreeManager design\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 17\n- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 6, Edit: 3, Grep: 1, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: coverage run (~50 lines), verbose test run (~40 lines), coverage run 2 (~30 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 9 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 17-3-run-command-parallel-integration — code-review (2026-04-04T21:03)\n\n- **HIGH**: 20+ TypeScript compilation errors in `run-parallel.test.ts` — mock types wrong, stale @ts-expect-error, spread argument patterns invalid. All fixed.\n- **HIGH**: Mock wrappers used `...(args as [])` cast that silently dropped arguments. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM**: `poolInstance.onEvent` accessed as `unknown` type. Fixed.\n- **LOW (unfixed)**: `executeFn` ignores `epicId` parameter — each worktree runs full workflow. Deferred to Epic 18/19.\n- **LOW (unfixed)**: `countStories` dual import/re-export pattern in `run.ts`.\n- Coverage: 96.7% overall (PASS), all files above 80% floor.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 24\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 9, Edit: 8, Grep: 3, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npx tsc --noEmit` (~30 lines), `git diff --name-only` (~29 lines), `git status --porcelain` (~21 lines)\n- Files read: 11 unique, 13 total reads (`run-parallel.test.ts` read 3x)\n- Redundant operations: TSC run 3 times for incremental fix verification\n\n---\n\n### 17-3-run-command-parallel-integration — dev-story (2026-04-04T20:55)\n\n- **Vitest mock pattern**: `vi.fn()` mocks cannot be used with `new` via `mockReturnValue`. Had to create actual ES classes in hoisted block that delegate to mutable factory functions. Non-obvious pattern.\n- **File length**: `run.ts` grew from 203 to 340 lines. Story notes NFR9 max 300 lines per file. Could extract parallel path to `run-parallel.ts`.\n- **No integration test with real LanePool/WorktreeManager**: All tests mock pool and worktree manager. Real end-to-end behavior not tested at this level.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 30\n- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 10, Edit: 18, Grep: 2, Write: 1, Glob: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npx tsc --noEmit` (~33 lines), `npx vitest run run-parallel.test.ts` (~40 lines), `npx vitest run` grep (~22 lines)\n- Files read: 10 unique, 11 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None significant\n\n---\n\n### 17-3-run-command-parallel-integration — create-story (2026-04-04T20:42)\n\n- No ambiguities in epic definition.\n- Workaround: `--resume` + parallel mode edge case not covered — deferred to Epic 18/19.\n- Risk: executeFn agent resolution is shared across worktrees — fine while agents are stateless config objects.\n- Observation: Docker pre-flight check preserved in parallel path (harmless but unnecessary).\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Bash: 1, Read: 7, Grep: 5, Write: 1, Glob: 5\n- Largest Bash outputs: `ls implementation-artifacts` (~230 lines)\n- Files read: 9 unique, 9 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None\n\n---\n\n### 17-2-lane-pool — verification (2026-04-04T20:31)\n\n- **`codeharness verify` precondition failure**: AGENTS.md for `src/lib` did not reference `lane-pool.ts`. Fixed by adding entry to AGENTS.md.\n- **BATS test warnings**: `npm test` output polluted with BW01 warnings from BATS integration tests. Pre-existing.\n- **Branch coverage 91.17%**: Uncovered branches at lines 291-306, 398 (defensive fallbacks). Stmts/funcs/lines all 100%.\n- **Verification gap**: AC5 (epic independence) verified by single test with 3 epics.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 14\n- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 3, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npx vitest run --coverage` (~80 lines), `npm test` (~60 lines)\n- Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads\n- Redundant operations: npm test ran twice, coverage command ran twice\n"}}
