{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012CEScWqqGFCq4Y2DMk4BYh","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story file created. Per the workflow instructions, I was told NOT to modify sprint-status.yaml and NOT to run git commit/add. The story is ready.\n\n---\n\n**Story Created:**\n- **Story ID:** 18.1\n- **Story Key:** 18-1-merge-serialization-execution\n- **File:** `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/18-1-merge-serialization-execution.md`\n- **Status:** ready-for-dev\n\n**What it covers:** Adds `mergeWorktree(epicId, strategy?)` to `WorktreeManager` with async mutex serialization, post-merge test suite execution, merge/rebase strategy support, and comprehensive `MergeResult` interface. 10 ACs, 6 tasks.\n\n**Verification tier breakdown:**\n- `test-provable`: 9 ACs (#1-6, #8-10) -- all verifiable via unit tests with mocked git/child_process\n- `runtime-provable`: 1 AC (#7) -- NFR4 timing constraint requires actual git operations\n\n**Next steps:**\n1. Review the story at the file path above\n2. Run `dev-story` for implementation\n3. Run `code-review` when complete\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **No project-context.md found** -- the workflow references `**/project-context.md` but none exists. Not a blocker; context was gathered from architecture and epics files.\n- **Sprint-status.yaml not updated** -- per user instruction, I did NOT update it from `backlog` to `ready-for-dev`. The workflow normally does this in step 6.\n- **No git commit/add** -- per user instruction, skipped.\n- **Web research step skipped** -- the story uses no new external libraries (only `node:child_process` and git CLI). No web research was needed.\n- **Workaround: mutex pattern** -- the architecture specifies a mutex but doesn't prescribe an implementation. I included an inline `AsyncMutex` class pattern rather than suggesting an npm dependency (e.g., `async-mutex`). This keeps the zero-external-dependency approach consistent with the existing codebase.\n- **Risk: AC #7 (NFR4 timing)** -- the 30-second NFR excludes the test suite but includes the git merge itself. In practice, merge timing depends on repo size and disk speed. The `runtime-provable` tier is correct since this cannot be verified purely by unit tests.\n- **Observation:** The `findBranchForEpic` method is currently private on `WorktreeManager`. The `mergeWorktree` method can call it internally since it will be a class method, so no visibility change is needed.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Read: 10, Grep: 3, Glob: 4, Bash: 2, Write: 1, Skill: 1 (but it delegated back, so effectively 0)\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `git log --oneline -10` (~10 lines), `git diff --stat` (~0 lines)\n- Files read: 12 unique, 12 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: None. Each read targeted a distinct file or range."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a8d9f158f91965052 (use SendMessage with to: 'a8d9f158f91965052' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 69218\ntool_uses: 31\nduration_ms: 216875</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"80ecde4e-3ccc-44de-925d-a2036bf845d1","uuid":"b4db820f-e40d-4f6f-8222-9c2fda611e8d","timestamp":"2026-04-03T21:17:15.280Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /create-story for story 18-1-merge-serialization-execution. The sprint-status.yaml is at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml in /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness. Auto-discover the next backlog story and create it. For each AC, append a verification tier tag using this decision tree:\n\n**Tier Decision Tree (append one `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tag per AC):**\n- `test-provable` — AC can be verified by building the project and running tests/linters/grep. No running app needed. Examples: 'function X exists', 'type Y is exported', 'test Z passes', 'file has <300 lines'.\n- `runtime-provable` — AC requires runnin