{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01HkcvQXXcgTFo8j5g1PpYsq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01TUXvwAKaxJJ8qiwGZREz7e","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/18-1-merge-serialization-execution.md","old_string":"- [ ] Task 1: Define `MergeResult` interface and `MergeStrategy` type (AC: #9)\n  - [ ] Add `MergeResult` interface to `src/lib/worktree-manager.ts` with all fields from AC #9\n  - [ ] Add `MergeStrategy` type alias: `'rebase' | 'merge-commit'`\n  - [ ] Export both from `worktree-manager.ts`\n\n- [ ] Task 2: Implement merge mutex (AC: #2)\n  - [ ] Create a simple async mutex class (or use a lightweight pattern — no external dependency)\n  - [ ] The mutex must be a module-level singleton shared across all `WorktreeManager` instances\n  - [ ] Pattern: `acquire()` returns a `release()` function; callers `await acquire()` and call `release()` in `finally`\n\n- [ ] Task 3: Implement `mergeWorktree(epicId, strategy?)` method (AC: #1, #6, #8, #10)\n  - [ ] Find the branch for the given epicId using `findBranchForEpic(epicId)`\n  - [ ] Acquire merge mutex\n  - [ ] If `strategy === 'rebase'`: run `git rebase {branch}` on main\n  - [ ] If `strategy === 'merge-commit'` (default): run `git merge --no-ff {branch}`\n  - [ ] Parse git output to detect conflicts (exit code + `--name-only` on `git diff --diff-filter=U`)\n  - [ ] On unexpected git errors: ensure main branch is restored (`git merge --abort` or `git rebase --abort`)\n  - [ ] Return `MergeResult`\n\n- [ ] Task 4: Implement post-merge test suite execution (AC: #3, #4, #5)\n  - [ ] After successful merge (no conflict), run `npm test` (or configurable test command) via `child_process.exec` with timeout\n  - [ ] Parse test results from stdout (pass/fail count, coverage if available)\n  - [ ] If tests pass: call `cleanupWorktree(epicId)`, return `MergeResult` with `success: true`\n  - [ ] If tests fail: run `git reset --hard HEAD~1` to revert merge, return `MergeResult` with `success: false, reason: 'tests-failed'`\n\n- [ ] Task 5: Wire merge strategy from `ExecutionConfig` (AC: #8)\n  - [ ] Accept `MergeStrategy` as parameter to `mergeWorktree`\n  - [ ] Default to `'merge-commit'` if not specified\n  - [ ] Lane pool or caller passes `execution.merge_strategy` from the resolved workflow\n\n- [ ] Task 6: Write unit tests (AC: #1-#10)\n  - [ ] Test: `mergeWorktree` calls `git merge --no-ff` for merge-commit strategy\n  - [ ] Test: `mergeWorktree` calls `git rebase` for rebase strategy\n  - [ ] Test: mutex serializes concurrent merge calls\n  - [ ] Test: clean merge + passing tests returns `success: true` and cleans up worktree\n  - [ ] Test: clean merge + failing tests reverts merge and returns `tests-failed`\n  - [ ] Test: conflict detected returns `conflicts` array and `reason: 'conflict'`\n  - [ ] Test: unexpected git error returns `reason: 'git-error'` and rolls back\n  - [ ] Test: `MergeResult` has correct shape with all required fields\n  - [ ] Test: default strategy is `merge-commit` when not specified\n  - [ ] Test: merge mutex is shared across instances (singleton)","new_string":"- [x] Task 1: Define `MergeResult` interface and `MergeStrategy` type (AC: #9)\n  - [x] Add `MergeResult` interface to `src/lib/worktree-manager.ts` with all fields from AC #9\n  - [x] Add `MergeStrategy` type alias: `'rebase' | 'merge-commit'`\n  - [x] Export both from `worktree-manager.ts`\n\n- [x] Task 2: Implement merge mutex (AC: #2)\n  - [x] Create a simple async mutex class (or use a lightweight pattern — no external dependency)\n  - [x] The mutex must be a module-level singleton shared across all `WorktreeManager` instances\n  - [x] Pattern: `acquire()` returns a `release()` function; callers `await acquire()` and call `release()` in `finally`\n\n- [x] Task 3: Implement `mergeWorktree(epicId, strategy?)` method (AC: #1