{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EUhaB3WQdRkzB3LAZYFXvq","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 18.1: Merge Serialization & Execution\n2\t\n3\tStatus: review\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a developer,\n10\tI want epic branches to merge into main one at a time with full test validation,\n11\tso that merged code is always tested and conflicts don't race.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** `worktree-manager.ts` already exists with `createWorktree` and `cleanupWorktree`, **when** the `mergeWorktree(epicId)` method is added, **then** it performs `git merge codeharness/epic-{N}-{slug}` on the main branch and returns a `MergeResult` indicating success or conflict. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n16\t\n17\t2. **Given** two epics complete concurrently and both call `mergeWorktree`, **when** merge is triggered, **then** a mutex ensures only one merge executes at a time — the second caller blocks until the first finishes. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n18\t\n19\t3. **Given** `mergeWorktree(epicId)` runs and `git merge` succeeds (no conflicts), **when** the merge completes, **then** the full test suite is executed on the merged main via `npm test` (or the project's configured test command). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t4. **Given** `git merge` succeeds and the test suite passes, **when** post-merge validation finishes, **then** the worktree is cleaned up via `cleanupWorktree(epicId)` and the `MergeResult` has `success: true` with test results (pass count, fail count, coverage). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n22\t\n23\t5. **Given** `git merge` succeeds but the test suite fails, **when** post-merge validation finishes, **then** the merge is reverted (`git reset --hard HEAD~1`), the `MergeResult` has `success: false`, `reason: 'tests-failed'`, and the worktree is preserved for investigation. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t6. **Given** `git merge` produces conflicts (exit code 1 with conflict markers), **when** merge conflict is detected, **then** `mergeWorktree` returns `MergeResult` with `success: false`, `reason: 'conflict'`, and `conflicts: string[]` listing the conflicting file paths. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n26\t\n27\t7. **Given** a non-conflicting merge, **when** measured end-to-end (merge + test suite), **then** the merge operation itself (excluding test suite) completes within 30 seconds (NFR4). <!-- verification: runtime-provable -->\n28\t\n29\t8. **Given** the workflow has `execution.merge_strategy: 'rebase'`, **when** `mergeWorktree` is called, **then** it uses `git rebase` instead of `git merge`. **And given** `execution.merge_strategy: 'merge-commit'` (the default), **when** `mergeWorktree` is called, **then** it uses `git merge --no-ff`. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n30\t\n31\t9. **Given** the `MergeResult` interface, **when** inspected, **then** it includes fields: `success: boolean`, `reason?: 'conflict' | 'tests-failed' | 'git-error'`, `conflicts?: string[]`, `testResults?: { passed: number; failed: number; coverage?: number }`, and `durationMs: number`. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n32\t\n33\t10. **Given** an unexpected git error during merge (not a conflict — e.g., branch not found, detached HEAD), **when** `mergeWorktree` catches the error, **then** `MergeResult` has `success: false`, `reason: 'git-error'`, and the main branch state is unchanged (rolled back if partially modified). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n36\t\n37\t- [x] Task 1: Define `MergeResult` interface and `MergeStrategy` type (AC: #9)\n38\t  - [x] Add `MergeResult` interface to `src/lib/worktree-manager.ts` with all fields from AC #9\n39\t  - [x] Add `MergeStrategy` type alias: `'rebase' | 'merge-commit'`\n40\t  - [x] Export both from `worktree-manager.ts`\n41\t\n42\t- [x] Task 2: Implement merge mutex (AC: #2)\n43\t  - [x] Create a simple async mutex class (or use a lightweight pattern — no external dependency)\n44\t  - [x] The mutex must be a module-level singleton shared across all `WorktreeManager` instances\n45\t  - [x] Pattern: `acquire()` returns a `release()` function; callers `await acquire()` and call `release()` in `finally`\n46\t\n47\t- [x] Task 3: Implement `mergeWorktree(epicId, strategy?)` method (AC: #1, #6, #8, #10)\n48\t  - [x] Find the branch for the given epicId using `findBranchForEpic(epicId)`\n49\t  - [x] Acquire merge mutex\n50\t  - [x] If `strategy === 'rebase'`: run `git rebase {branch}` on main\n51\t  - [x] If `strategy === 'merge-commit'` (default): run `git merge --no-ff {branch}`\n52\t  - [x] Parse git output to detect conflicts (exit code + `--name-only` on `git diff --diff-filter=U`)\n53\t  - [x] On unexpected git errors: ensure main branch is restored (`git merge --abort` or `git rebase --abort`)\n54\t  - [x] Return `MergeResult`\n55\t\n56\t- [x] Task 4: Implement post-merge test suite execution (AC: #3, #4, #5)\n57\t  - [x] After successful merge (no conflict), run `npm test` (or configurable test command) via `child_process.exec` with timeout\n58\t  - [x] Parse test results from stdout (pass/fail count, coverage if available)\n59\t  - [x] If tests pass: call `cleanupWorktree(epicId)`, return `MergeResult` with `success: true`\n60\t  - [x] If tests fail: run `git reset --hard HEAD~1` to revert merge, return `MergeResult` with `success: false, reason: 'tests-failed'`\n61\t\n62\t- [x] Task 5: Wire merge strategy from `ExecutionConfig` (AC: #8)\n63\t  - [x] Accept `MergeStrategy` as parameter to `mergeWorktree`\n64\t  - [x] Default to `'merge-commit'` if not specified\n65\t  - [x] Lane pool or caller passes `execution.merge_strategy` from the resolved workflow\n66\t\n67\t- [x] Task 6: Write unit tests (AC: #1-#10)\n68\t  - [x] Test: `mergeWorktree` calls `git merge --no-ff` for merge-commit strategy\n69\t  - [x] Test: `mergeWorktree` calls `git rebase` for rebase strategy\n70\t  - [x] Test: mutex serializes concurrent merge calls\n71\t  - [x] Test: clean merge + passing tests returns `success: true` and cleans up worktree\n72\t  - [x] Test: clean merge + failing tests reverts merge and returns `tests-failed`\n73\t  - [x] Test: conflict detected returns `conflicts` array and `reason: 'conflict'`\n74\t  - [x] Test: unexpected git error returns `reason: 'git-error'` and rolls back\n75\t  - [x] Test: `MergeResult` has correct shape with all required fields\n76\t  - [x] Test: default strategy is `merge-commit` when not specified\n77\t  - [x] Test: merge mutex is shared across instances (singleton)\n78\t\n79\t## Dev Notes\n80\t\n81\t### Architecture Constraints\n82\t\n83\t- **Architecture Decision 3** (architecture-parallel-execution.md): Merges are serialized — only one `git merge` into main at a time. Use a mutex pattern. Cross-worktree test validation runs after every merge.\n84\t- **Merge Safety Pattern**: Acquire mutex before any git operation on main. Run `git status` before merge to verify main is clean. On test failure: `git reset --hard HEAD~1`. On git error: `git merge --abort` / `git rebase --abort`.\n85\t- **WorktreeManager boundary**: The worktree manager knows git operations. It does NOT know about agents, stories, or TUI. The merge agent (story 18-2) will call `mergeWorktree` and handle conflict resolution separately.\n86\t\n87\t### Key Files to Modify\n88\t\n89\t| File | Why |\n90\t|------|-----|\n91\t| `src/lib/worktree-manager.ts` | Add `mergeWorktree()` method, `MergeResult` interface, `MergeStrategy` type, merge mutex |\n92\t| `src/lib/__tests__/worktree-manager.test.ts` | Add tests for all merge-related functionality |\n93\t\n94\t### Key Files to Read (Do Not Modify)\n95\t\n96\t| File | Why |\n97\t|------|-----|\n98\t| `src/lib/lane-pool.ts` | `LanePool`, `EpicResult` — the pool will call `mergeWorktree` after epic completion (wired in 18-2/19-1, not this story) |\n99\t| `src/lib/hierarchical-flow.ts` | `ExecutionConfig.merge_strategy` — provides the strategy choice |\n100\t| `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` | `EngineResult` — used in lane results, not directly by merge |\n101\t\n102\t### Implementation Patterns\n103\t\n104\t**Merge mutex (async, no external deps):**\n105\t```typescript\n106\tclass AsyncMutex {\n107\t  private locked = false;\n108\t  private waitQueue: Array<() => void> = [];\n109\t\n110\t  async acquire(): Promise<() => void> {\n111\t    while (this.locked) {\n112\t      await new Promise<void>((resolve) => this.waitQueue.push(resolve));\n113\t    }\n114\t    this.locked = true;\n115\t    return () => {\n116\t      this.locked = false;\n117\t      const next = this.waitQueue.shift();\n118\t      if (next) next();\n119\t    };\n120\t  }\n121\t}\n122\t\n123\t// Module-level singleton\n124\tconst mergeMutex = new AsyncMutex();\n125\t```\n126\t\n127\t**Merge execution:**\n128\t```typescript\n129\tasync mergeWorktree(epicId: string, strategy: MergeStrategy = 'merge-commit'): Promise<MergeResult> {\n130\t  const start = Date.now();\n131\t  const branch = this.findBranchForEpic(epicId);\n132\t  if (!branch) throw new WorktreeError(`No branch found for epic ${epicId}`, '');\n133\t\n134\t  const release = await mergeMutex.acquire();\n135\t  try {\n136\t    // Verify main is clean\n137\t    this.execGit('git status --porcelain');\n138\t\n139\t    // Perform merge or rebase\n140\t    try {\n141\t      if (strategy === 'rebase') {\n142\t        this.execGit(`git rebase ${branch}`);\n143\t      } else {\n144\t        this.execGit(`git merge --no-ff ${branch}`);\n145\t      }\n146\t    } catch (err) {\n147\t      // Detect conflict vs other error\n148\t      const conflicts = this.detectConflicts();\n149\t      if (conflicts.length > 0) {\n150\t        this.abortMerge(strategy);\n151\t        return { success: false, reason: 'conflict', conflicts, durationMs: Date.now() - start };\n152\t      }\n153\t      this.abortMerge(strategy);\n154\t      return { success: false, reason: 'git-error', durationMs: Date.now() - start };\n155\t    }\n156\t\n157\t    // Run test suite\n158\t    const testResults = await this.runTestSuite();\n159\t    if (testResults.failed > 0) {\n160\t      this.execGit('git reset --hard HEAD~1');\n161\t      return { success: false, reason: 'tests-failed', testResults, durationMs: Date.now() - start };\n162\t    }\n163\t\n164\t    // Success — cleanup\n165\t    this.cleanupWorktree(epicId);\n166\t    return { success: true, testResults, durationMs: Date.now() - start };\n167\t  } finally {\n168\t    release();\n169\t  }\n170\t}\n171\t```\n172\t\n173\t**Test suite execution:**\n174\t```typescript\n175\tprivate async runTestSuite(): Promise<{ passed: number; failed: number; coverage?: number }> {\n176\t  // Use child_process.exec (async) with timeout — not execSync\n177\t  // Parse JSON reporter output or stdout for pass/fail counts\n178\t}\n179\t```\n180\t\n181\t### Previous Story (17-3) Intelligence\n182\t\n183\t- Story 17-3 completed the run command parallel integration. The run command creates `WorktreeManager` and `LanePool`, builds epic descriptors from sprint state, and reports results.\n184\t- The `WorktreeManager` currently has `createWorktree`, `cleanupWorktree`, `listWorktrees`, and `detectOrphans`.\n185\t- The `execGit` private helper wraps `execSync` with error handling and 30s timeout. Reuse this for merge commands.\n186\t- Tests use `vi.mock('node:child_process')` to mock `execSync`. The merge tests will follow the same pattern.\n187\t- The `findBranchForEpic(epicId)` private method already exists — returns the branch name for a given epicId or undefined.\n188\t- Current test count: ~4850+ tests across 178+ files.\n189\t- Module patterns: TypeScript in `src/`, ESM with `.js` import extensions, vitest test framework.\n190\t\n191\t### Boundary: What This Story Does NOT Include\n192\t\n193\t- **Conflict resolution via merge agent** -- deferred to Story 18-2. This story detects conflicts and reports them but does NOT resolve them.\n194\t- **Cross-worktree test validation as a standalone module** -- deferred to Story 18-3. This story runs tests inline within `mergeWorktree`.\n195\t- **Epic state transitions** -- deferred to Epic 19. This story does not update epic state (completing, merging, etc).\n196\t- **TUI merge status display** -- deferred to Epic 20.\n197\t- **Wiring mergeWorktree into the lane pool completion flow** -- the lane pool and epic completion detector (19-1) will call `mergeWorktree`. This story adds the method; callers are wired later.\n198\t\n199\t### Edge Cases\n200\t\n201\t- **Branch not found for epicId**: `mergeWorktree` should return a git-error `MergeResult`, not throw.\n202\t- **Main branch is dirty** (uncommitted changes): `git status --porcelain` before merge; abort if non-empty.\n203\t- **Rebase with conflicts**: `git rebase` produces conflicts differently than `git merge`. Both paths must detect and abort correctly.\n204\t- **Test command not found**: `npm test` fails if no test script is defined. Treat as test failure (not git error).\n205\t- **Concurrent `cleanupWorktree` during merge**: The mutex prevents this — cleanup only happens after merge succeeds inside the mutex.\n206\t- **`git reset --hard HEAD~1` fails**: This would indicate a corrupted git state. Log the error but still return `tests-failed` result.\n207\t- **Empty branch (no commits)**: `git merge --no-ff` with no changes produces a no-op merge. Handle gracefully.\n208\t\n209\t### Project Structure Notes\n210\t\n211\t- Source: TypeScript in `src/`, compiled to `dist/`\n212\t- Tests: vitest, colocated in `src/lib/__tests__/` directories\n213\t- ESM modules — use `.js` extensions in imports\n214\t- Build: `npm run build`\n215\t- Test: `npm test`\n216\t- The `worktree-manager.ts` file is ~387 lines. Adding merge support will grow it but should stay under 500.\n217\t- The `child_process` mock pattern is already established in the test file.\n218\t\n219\t### References\n220\t\n221\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-parallel-execution.md#Story 18.1]\n222\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Decision 3 -- Merge Serialization & Agent]\n223\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Merge Safety Pattern]\n224\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md#FR12, FR13, FR16, FR17]\n225\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md#NFR4]\n226\t\n227\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n228\t## Verification Requirements\n229\t\n230\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/18-1-merge-serialization-execution-proof.md)\n231\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n232\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n233\t\n234\t## Documentation Requirements\n235\t\n236\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n237\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/18-1-merge-serialization-execution.md\n238\t\n239\t## Testing Requirements\n240\t\n241\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n242\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n243\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n244\t\n245\t## Dev Agent Record\n246\t\n247\t### Agent Model Used\n248\tClaude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n249\t\n250\t### Debug Log References\n251\tN/A\n252\t\n253\t### Completion Notes List\n254\t- All 6 tasks completed, all 10 ACs addressed\n255\t- 55 tests total (29 existing + 26 new merge tests), all passing\n256\t- Coverage: 98.35% statements, 91.17% branches, 100% functions, 98.84% lines\n257\t- Build succeeds cleanly\n258\t\n259\t### File List\n260\t- `src/lib/worktree-manager.ts` — added MergeResult, MergeStrategy, AsyncMutex, mergeMutex, mergeWorktree(), detectConflicts(), abortMerge(), runTestSuite(), parseTestOutput()\n261\t- `src/lib/__tests__/worktree-manager.test.ts` — added 26 tests covering all merge ACs\n262\t"}]},