{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XXhdphpWgbZji5vGv35nvf","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-04\n2\t\n3\t### 17-3-run-command-parallel-integration — verification (2026-04-04T01:10)\n4\t\n5\t- Proof document used `### AC N:` headers instead of `## AC N:` — validator couldn't parse. Fixed by rewriting proof.\n6\t- No `bash`+`output` code block pairs in original proof — added evidence blocks.\n7\t- Subagent misreported test compilation failure (Babel/Jest) when project uses vitest.\n8\t\n9\t## Token Report\n10\t- Total tool calls: 5\n11\t- By tool: Bash: 3, Read: 1, Write: 1\n12\t- Files read: 1 unique, 1 total reads\n13\t- Redundant operations: none\n14\t\n15\t### 18-1-merge-serialization-execution — create-story (2026-04-04T01:13)\n16\t\n17\t- No project-context.md found — context gathered from architecture and epics files.\n18\t- Workaround: inline AsyncMutex class pattern rather than npm dependency.\n19\t- Risk: AC #7 (NFR4 timing) depends on repo size/disk speed, tagged runtime-provable.\n20\t\n21\t## Token Report\n22\t- Total tool calls: 18\n23\t- By tool: Read: 10, Grep: 3, Glob: 4, Bash: 2, Write: 1\n24\t- Largest Bash outputs: `git log --oneline -10` (~10 lines)\n25\t- Files read: 12 unique, 12 total reads\n26\t- Redundant operations: none\n27\t\n28\t### 18-1-merge-serialization-execution — dev-story (2026-04-04T01:17)\n29\t\n30\t- Branch coverage gap (91.17%): defensive catch blocks hard to trigger in isolation.\n31\t- Test output parsing simplistic — regex for vitest/jest only, falls back for other runners.\n32\t- promisify mock coupling: tests depend on module's use of `promisify(exec)`.\n33\t\n34\t## Token Report\n35\t- Total tool calls: 16\n36\t- By tool: Read: 5, Edit: 7, Bash: 4, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n37\t- Largest Bash outputs: vitest coverage (~30 lines), vitest test (~10 lines)\n38\t- Files read: 6 unique, 7 total reads\n39\t- Redundant operations: none\n40\t\n41\t### 18-1-merge-serialization-execution — code-review (2026-04-04T01:22)\n42\t\n43\t- HIGH: Shell injection via testCommand parameter — fixed with regex validation.\n44\t- HIGH: Shell injection via malicious branch names — fixed with regex validation.\n45\t- MEDIUM: TOCTOU race on branch existence — fixed with re-verification inside mutex.\n46\t- MEDIUM: Missing `// IGNORE:` comment on catch block — fixed.\n47\t- LOW (unfixed): No mutex acquisition timeout — starvation risk.\n48\t- LOW (unfixed): No logging in merge path.\n49\t- LOW (unfixed): parseTestOutput only reads stdout, not stderr.\n50\t- Architecture: testCommand as raw shell string; safer would be execFile with array args.\n51\t\n52\t## Token Report\n53\t- Total tool calls: 16\n54\t- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 6, Edit: 3, Grep: 2, Glob: 1\n55\t- Largest Bash outputs: npm run test:coverage (~60 lines x2)\n56\t- Files read: 4 unique, 6 total reads (worktree-manager.test.ts read 4x)\n57\t- Redundant operations: test:coverage ran twice (once pre-fix, once post-fix)\n58\t\n59\t### 18-1-merge-serialization-execution — verification (2026-04-04T01:27)\n60\t\n61\t- BATS test failures (253 `not ok`): pre-existing, not related to story 18-1.\n62\t- AC 7 (runtime-provable) timing NFR4 can't be fully verified with mocked git ops — durationMs mechanism confirmed but 30-second bound untested.\n63\t- npm test ran 4 times in verification subagent (wasteful).\n64\t\n65\t## Token Report\n66\t- Total tool calls: 16\n67\t- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 3, Grep: 1, Write: 1, other: 1\n68\t- Largest Bash outputs: npm test (~40 lines), vitest verbose (~80 lines)\n69\t- Files read: 3 unique, 4 total reads\n70\t- Redundant operations: npm test ran 4 times to extract different parts\n71\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_015h16qvaXpY2Uov25AXUvc8","session_id":"80ecde4e-3ccc-44de-925d-a2036bf845d1","uuid":"e08d8eff-52f0-4a16-92e2-7487ef1da76a","timestamp":"2026-04-03T21:37:54.833Z"}
